The '''Governor's Cup''' is a trophy awarded to the victor of the annual [[college football]] game between the [[Kentucky Wildcats football|University of Kentucky]] and the [[University of Louisville]]; it is also used as a reference to the rivalry itself.<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/ncf/recap?gameId=282440097 Kentucky dumps archrival as defense denies Louisville trip to end zone, Associated Press]</ref> Though the teams first played in 1912<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/ncf/recap?gameId=282440097 Kentucky dumps archrival as defense denies Louisville trip to end zone, Associated Press],</ref> the Governor's Cup has been awarded every year since [[1994 in sports|1994]].
Kentucky leads the all time rivalry with 14 wins to Louisville's 10.<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/ncf/recap?gameId=282440097 Kentucky dumps archrival as defense denies Louisville trip to end zone Associated Press]</ref> Louisville currently holds the Governor's Cup.
